Agrokor, Mid Europa, Warburg Pincus Bid for Mercator

-- B y   B o r i s   C e r n i
-- 
2011-03-10T13:17:48Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-10/agrokor-mid-europa-warburg-pincus-bid-for-mercator-1-.html
Agrokor d.d. of  Croatia , Warburg
Pincus LLC and Mid Europa Partners Ltd. placed bids for a 23.3
percent stake in  Mercator Poslovni Sistem (MELR)  d.d., the biggest
publicly traded supermarket chain in the Balkans.    Pivovarna Lasko (PILR)  Group d.d., the seller of the stake in the
Slovenian retailer, commented on bids in an e-mail statement
today. Mercator shares surged the most in five months today
before the announcement was made.  Mercator continued to advance for a third consecutive day
in Ljubljana, gaining 6.95 euros ($9.61), or 4.2 percent, the
biggest advance since Oct. 13. The Slovenian company, based in
Ljubljana, is the best performer this year among the six
companies in the benchmark Slovenian SBITOP index. The stock
rose 8.4 percent this year, which compares with a 2.5 percent
decline of the main index.  Finance newspaper yesterday said that Agrokor, the largest
privately held group in the Balkans, submitted a bid for a stake
in Mercator yesterday as well as Mid Europa Partners, a London-
based private equity group.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Boris Cerni in Ljubljana at 
 bcerni@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
